cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.PL 

This paper is about using a clustering algorithm to improve the performance of Case-Based Reasoning (CBR) for software effort estimation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as clustering and analogies, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with data analysis and understanding the structure of a dataset, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
